If No then VS.VSSTAT = 'NOT DONE' when VS.VSTESTCD = 'VSALL'
Set to USUBJID in SDTM.DM domain.
Sequence Number given to ensure uniqueness of subject records within a domain. May be any valid number.
1. Clinical encounter number. 2. Numeric version of VISIT, used for sorting.
1. Protocol-defined description of clinical encounter. 2. May be used in addition to VISITNUM and/or VISITDY.
Epoch associated with the start date/time of the observation, or the date/time of collection if start date/time is not collected.

Taken directly from SDTM IG 3.1.2, p41: --DY = (date portion of --DTC) - (date portion of SDTM.DM.RFSTDTC) + 1 if --DTC is on or after SDTM.DM.RFSTDTC; --DY = (date portion of --DTC) - (date portion of SDTM.DM.RFSTDTC) if --DTC precedes SDTM.DM.RFSTDTC.
